    <dataqual>
        <attracc>
            <attraccr>State Route numbers and Accumulated Route Mileage values were obtained from the State Highway Log.</attraccr>
        </attracc>
        <logic>This data forms a network representing the connectivity of State Routes (SR's) for Washington state. This includes all State Routes, US Routes, Interstates, Frontage Roads, Ramps, Ferry Terminals and some Proposed routes located within the TRIPS database.</logic>
        <complete>The data set contains all of the state routes in the state of Washington. San Juan County contains no State Routes.</complete>
        <posacc>
            <horizpa>
                <horizpar>Positional accuracy of this data set has not been determined.</horizpar>
            </horizpa>
        </posacc>
        <lineage>
            <srcinfo>
                <typesrc>None</typesrc>
                <srccontr>Geometry depicting Washington State Highways, attributes, and measure values to create the various 24k LRSs. These sources have included: USGS 7.5 Minute Quadrangles WSDOT Interchange Diagrams WSDOT State Highway Log GPS Based LRS Orthoimagery from DNR, Nies Mapping Group, Inc., NAIP, and the WSDOT Photogrammerty Office For more detailed information about these sources contact the data steward.</srccontr>
            </srcinfo>
            <procstep>
                <procdesc>A directional indicator ( i or d ) was added to the SR24kLRS datasets and then merged into one featureclass.</procdesc>
                <procdate>20240322</procdate>
